en picks a second counter at random.\n\n(a) Complete the tree diagram.\n\n(b) Find the probability that both counters are green.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":3},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"complete"},{"id":"0580-2025MayJune-Paper11-Q20","paper":"2025MayJune-Paper11","qnum":20,"marks":4,"topics":["Number","Statistics"],"s":"1.9","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Estimation","qtype":"estimation and rounding","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/M/J/25 Q20","year":2025,"session":"MayJune","tex":"The scatter diagram shows the price of petrol per litre and the number of litres sold at a petrol station on each of ten days.\n\n(a) These are the results for two more days.\n\nPlot this information on the scatter diagram.\n\n(b) What type of correlation is shown in the scatter diagram?\n\n(c) (i) On the scatter diagram, draw a line of best fit.\n\n(ii) One day the price of petrol was \\$1.55 per litre.\n\nUse your line of best fit to estimate the number of litres sold.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":1},{"label":"(c)","marks":1}],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"draw"},{"id":"0580-2025MayJune-Paper11-Q21","paper":"2025MayJune-Paper11","qnum":21,"marks":2,"topics":["Geometry"],"s":"4.6","d":1,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Angles","qtype":"angle calculations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/M/J/25 Q21","year":2025,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Points $A$, $B$ and $C$ lie on the circle, centre $O$.\n\nWork out angle $BCA$.","parts":[],"hasFigure":true,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2025MayJune-Paper11-Q22","paper":"2025MayJune-Paper11","qnum":22,"marks":3,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.1","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Types of number","qtype":"types of number","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/M/J/25 Q22","year":2025,"session":"MayJune","tex":"$A = 2^3 \\times 3$\n\n$B = 3^2 \\times 5$\n\n(a) Find the highest common factor (HCF) of $A$ and $B$.\n\n(b) Find the lowest common multiple (LCM) of $A$ and $B$.","part